"content": "<p>Cows, in OT times, often symbolised wealth and material well-being.</p>\n<h2>Cows as evidence of prosperity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job21:10\">JOB 21:10</a></strong> <em>Part of Job's complaint about the prosperity of the wicked.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:16\">GEN 12:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:35\">GEN 24:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:5\">GEN 32:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:13-Gen32:15\">GEN 32:13–32:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:1-Gen41:4\">GEN 41:1–41:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:17-Gen41:21\">GEN 41:17–41:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:25-Gen41:27\">GEN 41:25–41:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:2\">2SA 12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:27-2Chr32:28\">2CH 32:27–32:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:10\">PSA 50:10</a> <em>evidence of God's wealth</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:17-Hab3:18\">HAB 3:17–3:18</a> <em>the believer's joy despite the absence of prosperity</em></p>\n<h2>In the history of Israel</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:7-1Sam6:14\">1SA 6:7–6:14</a></p>\n<h2>Cows in God's new earth</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:7\">ISA 11:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:23\">ISA 30:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:20\">ISA 32:20</a></p>\n<h2>Cows as a source of nourishment and fuel</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam17:29\">2SA 17:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek4:15\">EZK 4:15</a></p>\n<h2>Laws concerning cows</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:30\">EXO 22:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:28\">LEV 22:28</a></p>\n<h2>Cows in metaphors</h2>\n<h3>Of stupidity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job18:3\">JOB 18:3</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Of godless women</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:1\">AMO 4:1</a></strong></p>",
